  </ul>

  <h2 id="key-terms">Key Terms</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Dysphagia:</strong> Difficulty swallowing — major aspiration risk factor.</li>
    <li><strong>Enteral nutrition:</strong> Nutrient delivery via the GI tract (feeding tube).</li>
    <li><strong>TPN:</strong> Total parenteral nutrition — IV delivery of nutrients bypassing the GI tract.</li>
    <li><strong>NEX measurement:</strong> Nose–Earlobe–Xiphoid — method to estimate NG tube insertion length.</li>
    <li><strong>Residual volume:</strong> Amount of formula remaining in stomach before next feeding; checked to assess gastric emptying.</li>
    <li><strong>IDDSI:</strong> International Dysphagia Diet Standardisation Initiative — framework for texture-modified foods and thickened liquids.</li>
  </ul>
